{"primaryContentSections":[{"content":[{"text":"Overview","anchor":"overview","type":"heading","level":2},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"😱 “No Overview Available!”","type":"text"}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"Be the hero to change that by watching the video or reading the transcript on WWDCIndex and providing notes! It’s super easy:","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"isActive":true,"identifier":"https:\/\/wwdcnotes.com\/documentation\/wwdcnotes\/contributing","type":"reference"}]},{"text":"Related Sessions","anchor":"Related-Sessions","type":"heading","level":2},{"style":"list","type":"links","items":["doc:\/\/WWDCNotes\/documentation\/WWDCNotes\/WWDC16-405-Whats-New-in-LLVM","doc:\/\/WWDCNotes\/documentation\/WWDCNotes\/WWDC16-410-Visual-Debugging-with-Xcode","doc:\/\/WWDCNotes\/documentation\/WWDCNotes\/WWDC16-412-Thread-Sanitizer-and-Static-Analysis","doc:\/\/WWDCNotes\/documentation\/WWDCNotes\/WWDC16-413-Introduction-to-Xcode"]}],"kind":"content"}],"identifier":{"interfaceLanguage":"swift","url":"doc:\/\/WWDCNotes\/documentation\/WWDCNotes\/WWDC16-417-Debugging-Tips-and-Tricks"},"kind":"article","abstract":[{"text":"Spend an hour with the team responsible for the technology behind Xcode’s debugger: LLDB. Find out what’s new, what’s been there all along that you didn’t know about, and how best to take advantage of it all. This session will cover a range of topics with tips for both newcomers and experienced developers.","type":"text"}],"hierarchy":{"paths":[["doc:\/\/WWDCNotes\/documentation\/WWDCNotes","doc:\/\/WWDCNotes\/documentation\/WWDCNotes\/WWDC16"]]},"sampleCodeDownload":{"action":{"type":"reference","identifier":"https:\/\/nonstrict.eu\/wwdcindex\/wwdc2016\/417\/","isActive":true,"overridingTitle":"Open on WWDCIndex"},"kind":"sampleDownload"},"metadata":{"modules":[{"name":"WWDC Notes"}],"title":"Debugging Tips and Tricks","roleHeading":"WWDC16","role":"sampleCode"},"schemaVersion":{"major":0,"patch":0,"minor":3},"sections":[],"variants":[{"traits":[{"interfaceLanguage":"swift"}],"paths":["\/documentation\/wwdcnotes\/wwdc16-417-debugging-tips-and-tricks"]}],"references":{"doc://WWDCNotes/documentation/WWDCNotes/WWDC16":{"title":"WWDC16","abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"Xcode 8, Swift 3.0, iOS 10, macOS 10.12 (Sierra), tvOS 10, watchOS 3."}],"kind":"article","identifier":"doc:\/\/WWDCNotes\/documentation\/WWDCNotes\/WWDC16","role":"collectionGroup","images":[{"type":"icon","identifier":"WWDC16-Icon.png"},{"type":"card","identifier":"WWDC16.jpeg"}],"url":"\/documentation\/wwdcnotes\/wwdc16","type":"topic"},"doc://WWDCNotes/documentation/WWDCNotes/WWDC16-412-Thread-Sanitizer-and-Static-Analysis":{"abstract":[{"text":"Xcode 8 makes it easier to find several new categories of bugs with improvements in Runtime Sanitization and the Clang Static Analyzer. The Thread Sanitizer will help you find data races and other concurrency bugs. The static analyzer has been extended to search for localizability issues, check nullability, and find memory leaks in MRR code.","type":"text"}],"role":"sampleCode","type":"topic","kind":"article","url":"\/documentation\/wwdcnotes\/wwdc16-412-thread-sanitizer-and-static-analysis","identifier":"doc:\/\/WWDCNotes\/documentation\/WWDCNotes\/WWDC16-412-Thread-Sanitizer-and-Static-Analysis","title":"Thread Sanitizer and Static Analysis"},"https://nonstrict.eu/wwdcindex/wwdc2016/417/":{"type":"download","url":"https:\/\/nonstrict.eu\/wwdcindex\/wwdc2016\/417\/","identifier":"https:\/\/nonstrict.eu\/wwdcindex\/wwdc2016\/417\/","checksum":null},"WWDCNotes.png":{"type":"image","variants":[{"url":"\/images\/WWDCNotes\/WWDCNotes.png","traits":["1x","light"]}],"alt":null,"identifier":"WWDCNotes.png"},"doc://WWDCNotes/documentation/WWDCNotes/WWDC16-413-Introduction-to-Xcode":{"title":"Introduction to Xcode","role":"sampleCode","kind":"article","type":"topic","abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"Xcode enables you to create great apps for Apple platforms. This session will introduce you to the basics of creating a project with Xcode, and more. You’ll learn how to comfortably navigate your project and gain insights into working with workspaces, targets, and schemes. We’ll introduce you to version control workflows, and walk through using Xcode’s source editors and design tools. Join us if you’re new to Apple platforms or want to learn more about using Xcode."}],"identifier":"doc:\/\/WWDCNotes\/documentation\/WWDCNotes\/WWDC16-413-Introduction-to-Xcode","url":"\/documentation\/wwdcnotes\/wwdc16-413-introduction-to-xcode"},"doc://WWDCNotes/documentation/WWDCNotes/WWDC16-405-Whats-New-in-LLVM":{"title":"What’s New in LLVM","kind":"article","url":"\/documentation\/wwdcnotes\/wwdc16-405-whats-new-in-llvm","role":"sampleCode","identifier":"doc:\/\/WWDCNotes\/documentation\/WWDCNotes\/WWDC16-405-Whats-New-in-LLVM","abstract":[{"text":"The Apple LLVM compiler in Xcode 8 adds new language features, improved diagnostics, and more powerful optimizations. Get an overview of some new Objective-C and C++ features and learn how to use advanced optimizations to speed up your apps.","type":"text"}],"type":"topic"},"doc://WWDCNotes/documentation/WWDCNotes":{"identifier":"doc:\/\/WWDCNotes\/documentation\/WWDCNotes","type":"topic","role":"collection","kind":"symbol","images":[{"type":"icon","identifier":"WWDCNotes.png"}],"url":"\/documentation\/wwdcnotes","abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"Session notes shared by the community for the community."}],"title":"WWDC Notes"},"doc://WWDCNotes/documentation/WWDCNotes/WWDC16-410-Visual-Debugging-with-Xcode":{"type":"topic","kind":"article","url":"\/documentation\/wwdcnotes\/wwdc16-410-visual-debugging-with-xcode","identifier":"doc:\/\/WWDCNotes\/documentation\/WWDCNotes\/WWDC16-410-Visual-Debugging-with-Xcode","title":"Visual Debugging with Xcode","role":"sampleCode","abstract":[{"text":"Discover Xcode’s enhancements for debugging autolayout issues at runtime. Learn how issues inside complex GKStateMachine objects can be easily debugged at runtime. Gain insight into finding performance bottlenecks inside SpriteKit and SceneKit apps more easily with the enhanced FPS gauge. Understand how to fix leaked and abandoned memory in your app by inspecting the heap from within your typical Xcode debugging workflow.","type":"text"}]},"WWDC16-Icon.png":{"type":"image","alt":null,"variants":[{"traits":["1x","light"],"url":"\/images\/WWDCNotes\/WWDC16-Icon.png"}],"identifier":"WWDC16-Icon.png"},"WWDC16.jpeg":{"type":"image","variants":[{"traits":["1x","light"],"url":"\/images\/WWDCNotes\/WWDC16.jpeg"}],"alt":null,"identifier":"WWDC16.jpeg"},"https://wwdcnotes.com/documentation/wwdcnotes/contributing":{"type":"link","titleInlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Learn More…"}],"title":"Learn More…","url":"https:\/\/wwdcnotes.com\/documentation\/wwdcnotes\/contributing","identifier":"https:\/\/wwdcnotes.com\/documentation\/wwdcnotes\/contributing"}}}